STR while also important probably isn't worth that much either, since we can buff our str nice and high, and our stuff doesn't weight that much.  I am never near being encumbered.  In the high end game you will find resists much more important that some of these other stats.  Magic is probably most important because most stuff goes against magic.  Fire, cold and poison I would rank all equal.  Once you start fighting dragons a lot you'll see its good to be able to get any one of these plus magic as high as possible.  Disease is really only used on perhaps a few keys mobs in the game and is easily boosted with a stein of moggok and a gullerback mantle as well as BD stuff and an amulet of undead protection/dragon talisman.<br>
<br>
Just my observation <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucalahad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calahad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/5/01 7:27:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bryll's Compilation and Comparison Chart</span><hr size=1> Idol of Karana (primary/secondary/range)<br>
